The paper deals with image-to-image translation and domain adaptation, which are both topics related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of neural networks and machine learning techniques, which are common in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of web-crawled data, which could fall under the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR) or web search (cs.WS). Finally, the paper deals with self-supervised learning, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM).
